      "side": 1,
      "message": "hasActiveCalls() already keys on the earliest call signal the daemon exposes to the client (CallService observes the call from the daemon\u0027s incoming-call callback at RINGING, well before answer), and treats null/non-terminal conference states as active. The remaining gap — push received, ICE/SIP negotiation still in flight, no call object yet — is exactly what the call grace window covers: it is not a heuristic guess but sized from on-device measurement of cold proxy reconnect + negotiation (~10-20s worst case observed) with a 3-6x margin at 60s, and the runnable re-checks hasActiveCalls() when the window expires, so any negotiation that has produced a RINGING call by then keeps the accounts up. A pending-connection signal from the daemon (e.g. surfacing pendingCalls_/channel requests through JNI) does not exist in the current client API; adding one is daemon-side work that we agree would make this airtight, but it belongs in a follow-up patch rather than this client-side change. Note also that deactivation does not tear down established channels: setAccountActive(false) with shutdownConnections\u003dfalse keeps existing connections alive (Manager::setAccountActive -\u003e doUnregister(false)), so a negotiation that completed channel setup survives even the worst-case timing.",
      "parentUuid": "c8619847_8a21fd07",
